  <datafield tag="545" ind1="1" ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">The Human Rights Party (HRP) of Ann Arbor was a radical socialist third party that influenced local politics in the period 1971 to 1975. The party grew out of the Radical Independent Party (founded 1970) and was renamed Socialist Human Rights Party in 1976.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="520" ind1="2" ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">The record group contains organizational and campaign documents of several parties including predecessor and successor parties to HRP. Campaign materials, platforms, position statements and numerous newspaper clippings along with committee and meeting minutes form the bulk of the records of this activist organization.</subfield>
